# ── GitHub Pages (site) + home PC (data) ─────────────────────────────────────
#
# 1. On your computer: copy server/.env.example → server/.env, set POKEFOLIO_TOKEN
# 2. Run on PC: npm run sync:server
# 3. Expose port 3456 with HTTPS (GitHub Pages is https — http will be blocked)
#    Easiest: Cloudflare Tunnel → https://developers.cloudflare.com/cloudflare-one/
# 4. GitHub repo → Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions → New secret:
#      VITE_SYNC_URL  = your public https URL (e.g. https://pokefolio.example.com)
#      VITE_SYNC_TOKEN = same value as POKEFOLIO_TOKEN in server/.env
# 5. Push to main — deploy rebuilds the site with sync enabled
#
# Live app: https://chuchinator.github.io/pokemon-app/
# Server CORS must allow: https://chuchinator.github.io  (see server/.env.example)

# Local dev (optional — Vite proxies /api to localhost:3456):
# VITE_SYNC_URL=http://localhost:3456
# VITE_SYNC_TOKEN=your-secret

# GitHub Actions injects VITE_SYNC_* from secrets — you do not need them in .env for deploy.
